27 determine whether any person is a teacher as defined in this Chapter. On and
28 after August 1, 2001, a person who is a nonimmigrant alien and who otherwise
29 meets the requirements of this subdivision shall not be excluded from the
30 definition of "teacher" solely because the person holds a temporary or
31 time-limited visa. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the term "teacher" shall not
32 include any nonimmigrant alien employed in elementary or secondary public
33 schools, whether employed in a full-time, part-time, temporary, permanent, or
34 substitute teacher position, and participating in an exchange visitor program
35 designated by the United States Department of State pursuant to 22 C.F.R.
36 Part 62 or by the United States Department of Homeland Security pursuant to
37 8 C.F.R. Part 214.2(q).
38 (26) "Year" as Year. – As used in this Article shall mean the regular fiscal year
39 beginning July 1 and ending June 30 in the following calendar year unless
40 otherwise defined by regulation of the Board of Trustees."
41 SECTION 5.1.(b) This section is effective when it becomes law and applies to
42 determinations under Article 1 of Chapter 135 of the General Statutes made on or after that date.
43
44 PART VI. TECHNICAL CORRECTIONS
45
46 POST-RELEASE SUPERVISION ELIGIBILITY AND PROCEDURE
